Red meat prices have [risen dramatically
](http://www.zawya.com/Story.cfm/sidZAWYA20100418101043/Egyptians%20boycott%20red%20meat%20due%20to%20astronomical%20prices)
in Egypt in recent weeks. Whether or not it's related to the current state of
the global economy, it clear that many Egyptians are being pushed towards
vegetarianism due to the high prices. Lately, there have even been calls by
citizens to boycott meat in hopes that such activity may help lower prices.

[![Meat market near Ataba, Egypt - by Furibond on
Flickr](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/04/meatmarket-300x225.jpg)](http://www.flickr.com/photos/furibond/2186374166/in/photostream/)

Meat market near Ataba, Egypt – by Furibond on Flickr

_Masr Al Youm_ [reported the news](http://masr-
alyom.blogspot.com/2010/04/blog-post_3067.html) in his blog [Ar] on April 15.

تبدأ جمعيات حماية المستهلك، اليوم، إطلاق حملتها لمقاطعة استهلاك اللحوم فى
القاهرة وجميع المحافظات، احتجاجاً على ارتفاع أسعار اللحوم البلدية.

The Consumer Protection Association will start a meat boycott campaign today
in Cairo and all the other Egyptian provinces. This campaign is meant to show
protest and disagreement with the high prices of meat.

_Weekite_ then [wrote](http://weekite.blogspot.com/2010/04/boycott-meat.html)
[Ar] about how red meat prices have fluctuated during the past few years.

الطريقة اللي بيشتغل بيها السوق  
إنك لما تلاقي السعر مش مناسب ليك  
إنك تقلل من الاستهلاك شوية  
طبعاً احنا كل ما يزيد سعر اللحمة نشتري برده عادي  
لحد ما كيلو اللحمة وصل  
30 جنيه  
وبعدين 40  
50  
قلنا لأ بأه  
مش ممكن يزيد عن كده  
بأه 60  
وبعدين 70  
سبعين جنيه كيلو اللحمة ولا مؤاخذة؟  
ليه؟

The way markets work, when the prices of some goods become higher, you just
stop or reduce the quantity you buy of it. But here we have continued to
purchase meat normally despite of any price changes.

